;Numerically solves for the theta derivative of the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre functions;   N:       Degree of the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre function;   M:       Order of the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre function;   N and M can be arbritary as long as M le N, 0 ge M ge N, N ge 1;   ;INRAD=1 if InTheta is given in radians.;   InTheta: The angle (in degrees, unless specified by INRAD keyword)  ;   ;;written by Peter Kollmann, inspired byDrake A. Ranquist's dPdtheta procedure;TEST example;n=2 & m=2 & inTheta=1 & print,dPdtheta( n, m, inTheta,inrad=1) & print,dPdtheta2( n, m, inTheta,inrad=1)function dPdtheta2, n, m, inTheta, INRAD=inRadIF NOT KEYWORD_SET(inRad) THEN inRad=0theta = inThetaIF NOT inRad THEN theta = inTheta*!Pi/180theI=inTheta-0.2;IF theI lt 0 THEN theI=0theO=inTheta+0.2;IF theO gt !dPi THEN theO=!dPiThetaFull=vecgen(1000,theI,theO)PnmFull=getLegendre2( n, m, ThetaFull, INRAD=inRad)dPdT=deriv(ThetaFull,PnmFull)idx=whereApprox(ThetaFull,inTheta)return,dPdT[idx]END